snippet.textDisplay: Its very interesting how the narrative is all about AC Milan yet almost no words are spoken about how potent and dangerous Atalanta BC are. They have been playing the past 10 weeks or so sans Zapata [remember HIM?] and at times sans Illicic and Gomez otherwise they would be right at the front of Serie A. Hence their position on The Table requires a footnote . Guardiola said playing Atalanta was like "going to the dentist" while veteran Juventus GK Buffon stated that on their day "Atalanta can defeat anybody". Gosens is a rising star and others such as Malyinovsky and Pasalic are just getting going and fitting in.
